This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a framework for computing confidence intervals for individual predictions using deep learning techniques. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields heavily rely on deep learning architectures. Additionally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be possible sub-categories as the paper discusses techniques for improving the trust and interpretability of virtual screening models in drug discovery.
